This paper discusses the construction of functions using a hierarchy of simpler functions through compositions, which can be characterized by a binary rooted tree. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category, as it deals with the representation and manipulation of trees. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category, as it discusses the complexity of constructing functions using compositions of simpler functions. The paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories, as the construction of functions through compositions is a common technique in these fields. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category, as it discusses the representation and manipulation of information using trees.
